    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1204609011f39182",
      "text": "A [[system]] is defined by a boundary between itself and its environment ([[social environment]]), dividing it from an infinitely complex, or (colloquially) chaotic, exterior. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "e5a93f7c94813aaf",
      "text": "The interior of the system is thus a zone of reduced complexity: Communication within a system operates by selecting only a limited amount of all information available outside. This process is also called \"reduction of complexity\"."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "01ebcf91-ef82-45b0-b86c-269553373d72",
