    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "7abcdbf8b75afc10",
      "text": "Furthermore, each system has a distinctive identity that is constantly reproduced in its communication and depends on what is considered meaningful and what is not. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b09eb5078d0212cd",
      "text": "If a system fails to maintain that identity, it ceases to exist as a system and dissolves back into the environment it emerged from. Luhmann called this process of reproduction from elements previously filtered from an over-complex environment [[autopoiesis]]. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
