      "text": "The supreme criterion guiding the \"self-creation\" of any given system is a defining [[binary code]]. This binary code, is not to be confused with the computers operation: Luhmann (following Spencer-Brown and [[Gregory Bateson]]) assumes that auto-referential systems are continuously confronted with the dilemma of disintegration /continuation. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "c759f4b08fbc5528",
      "text": "This dilemma is framed with an ever-changing set of available choices; everyone of those potential choices can be the system's selection or not (a binary state, selected/rejected). The influence of Spencer-Brown's book, ''[[Laws of Form]]'', on Luhmann can hardly be overestimated."
